<HEAD>Reports President Stroessner Hospitalized, Government Won't
Comment</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASUNCION, Paraguay (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Alfredo Stroessner
reportedly has undergone prostate surgery and was hospitalized, but
the government on Monday refused comment.
   Juan Jose Benitez Rickmann, subsecretary for information and
worship, acknowleged that the 75-year-old Stroessner recently
received a medical checkup in preparation for his trip next month
to Taiwan. He said the general was in good health.
   But Benitez Rickmann did not respond to a question by a reporter
from Radio Caritas who asked about reports that Stroessner had
undergone surgery for a prostate problem and is a patient at the
National Institute for Social Health.
   Stroessner is the longest-ruling chief executive in the Western
Hemisphere. He came to power in a coup in 1954, was elected
president that year and has been re-elected more than a half dozen
times.
