<1ST_LINE>r i AM-NorthernIreland     09-05 0079</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Northern Ireland,0079</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Seize Machine Guns, Arrest Two Men</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested two men Monday
and seized parts for homemade machine guns apparently for use by
Protestant extremists.
   A police spokesman, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the
gun parts were seized in a search of farmland and buildings near
Ballynahinch, 15 miles south of Belfast.
   He said, ``the material would appear to be for homemade machine
guns for a Loyalist (Protestant) organization.''
</TEXT>
